    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Types of construction that use a skeleton of assembled wooden members, such as studs, joists, and rafters to support the building's floors, walls, and roof; in the field of insurance, buildings for which walls, partitions, floors, and roof are wholly or partly made of wood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
